	)
	(text "- The USB HSDM, HSDP, uHSDM, and uHSDP traces are differential pairs with 90 Ohms as differential\n   pairs, or 45 Ohms single ended.\n- The P and N pins for the CSI peripheral are also differential pairs, with 100 Ohms between each,\n   and 50 Ohms between each and ground.\n- USB C Power Delivery will be used, but may be disabled by unsoldering D5. A jumper will be\n   accessible to toggle the board from USB device/host modes. 5V input voltage will be provided\n   on VBUS if acting as the host. \n- Unlike the MX25 Flash chip, NRST is internally pulled up via a 40k Ohm resistor. Thus, H-L time\n   constant is 1ms, and L-H is 4ms."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 161.29 130.556 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "8da0dc3e-65f0-4ff9-ae51-0765d6de039c")
	)
